Usually just:
  sudo apt -y install ocaml
but if that is ocaml 4.01, do
  sudo apt -y remove ocaml
and see below.

To install Ocaml 4.02 before it arrives in the main Ubuntu repositories:
 * technique 1:
    sudo add-apt-repository -y ppa:avsm/ocaml42+opam12
    sudo apt update
    sudo apt -y install ocaml
   After using ocaml (to build unison, in my case), I can go back to normal repositories (which is necessary to install hevea), by doing:
    sudo apt -y remove ocaml
    sudo add-apt-repository -r -y ppa:avsm/ocaml42+opam12
    sudo apt update
 * technique 2 (Pavel recommends against it):
    sudo apt remove ocaml
    sudo apt install opam
    opam init
    opam switch 4.02.3
